#: ../../../driver-api/wmi.rst:5
msgid "WMI Driver API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/wmi.rst:7
msgid ""
"The WMI driver core supports a more modern bus-based interface for "
"interacting with WMI devices, and an older GUID-based interface. The latter "
"interface is considered to be deprecated, so new WMI drivers should "
"generally avoid it since it has some issues with multiple WMI devices "
"sharing the same GUID. The modern bus-based interface instead maps each WMI "
"device to a :c:type:`struct wmi_device <wmi_device>`, so it supports WMI "
"devices sharing the same GUID. Drivers can then register a :c:type:`struct "
"wmi_driver <wmi_driver>` which will be bound to compatible WMI devices by "
"the driver core."
msgstr ""

